Sure!

We could also have `EventTimeTimer`/`ProcessingTimeTimer` instead of `RelativeTimer`/`AbsoluteTimer` and get rid of the time domain in user space. I think your solution is good, though.

I think another question is whether to silently ignore absolute processing-time timers or throw an exception. I would be in favour of throwing an exception to make it clear to users what is happening.
